    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nThe maximum size in characters of a sign is hardcoded to 2.\n\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/6dee1672ccc973f50e28e4adb7cbadd481db3f03/src/nvim/types_defs.h#L57\n\nThe sign column width is a multiple of `SIGN_WIDTH` so it's 2 at the minimum.\n\nThis issue has been discussed before #13098 #990 #9788, but the focus was on `opt.signcolumn`.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nAdd `opt.signwidth` (default 2) so the user can choose the multiplier.\n\nWould not interfere with defaults and `opt.signcolumn`. I can try a PR myself.",
